      "freeform_prompt": "@frankekn Addressed the P2 finding about binding marker lookup to snapshot source identity. **What was added** Two new regression tests in `src/agents/model-auth.test.ts`: 1. **\"does not share file SecretRef runtime credentials across caller configs with the same provider id\"** - Source config has provider `shared-provider` with a file SecretRef and a resolved runtime credential. - A different caller config uses the same provider id and the same file SecretRef object, but a different `baseUrl`. - The test proves the runtime credential is **not** inherited, so structured non-env SecretRefs are bound to source snapshot identity. 2. **\"resolves normalized managed markers from the active runtime snapshot even when source identity drifts\"** - Source config has provider `normalized-provider` with `apiKey: NON_ENV_SECRETREF_MARKER`. - A drifted caller config uses the same provider id and the same marker, but a different `baseUrl`. - The test proves the normalized marker still resolves from the active runtime snapshot, preserving the intended normalized-marker fallback. This makes the isolation rule explicit: - Structured file/exec SecretRefs → bound to the source snapshot identity. - Normalized `secretref-managed` marker → delegates to the active runtime snapshot, matching how the secrets runtime prepares it. **Canonical fix request** There are two competing PRs for issue #92097: #92113 (this branch) and #92208. This PR absorbs the broader detection and precedence fixes from #92235 while preserving the normalized-marker fallback. Given the test coverage now isolates structured refs and documents the marker fallback, please consider this the canonical fix. Latest verification: - `pnpm test src/agents/model-auth.test.ts --run` — 69 passed - `pnpm check:test-types` — passed - `npx oxlint --import-plugin --config .oxlintrc.json src/agents/model-auth.ts src/agents/model-auth.test.ts` — clean - `npx oxfmt --write --threads=1 src/agents/model-auth.ts src/agents/model-auth.test.ts` — clean - `node --import tsx scripts/repro/issue-92097-secretref-custom-provider.mts` — PASS",
